  "original_title": "\u0b90.\u0b8e\u0bae\u0bcd.\u0b8e\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbe \u0b86\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1: \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc7\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "What's wrong with IMF talk: Question in the House of Opposition",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The international media has reported that the discussions with the representatives of the International Monetary Fund have failed and the opposition party has demanded in the parliament that the government should disclose the actual situation in this regard.",
        "This was the request made by United People's Power Member of Parliament Laxman Kiriella, who presented an intervening question during the oral questions held yesterday (4) in Parliament.",
        "The government was in discussions with the International Monetary Fund. The people of the country are very much looking forward to the outcome of this discussion. We expected the government to inform Parliament about this.",
        "But he said that no such announcement was made, and the international media had reported that the government's negotiations with the International Monetary Fund had failed. Especially the American media reported it. So we need to know about its true nature.",
        "At this time, the responding Minister Bandula Gunawardena, officials including President, Finance Minister and Central Bank Governor were engaged in several rounds of negotiations with the International Monetary Fund team. He said the Prime Minister would inform Parliament about the progress of these talks."
      ],
